h3. Issue Summary

When a page with an unpublished draft is updated via REST API, the subsequent attempt to edit the page will result in the shared draft to produce text that is a combination of the unpublished draft + the latest version of the page.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a page with the text "confluence".
 # Edit the page and replace the text to "jira".
 # Close the editor and let it remain as an unpublished draft.
 # Run an API call ({{PUT rest/api/content/12345}}) to update this page to the text "bitbucket".
{code:java}
{
    "id": "12345",
    "status": "current",
    "version": {
        "number": 2
    },
    "space": {
        "key": "TEST"
    },
    "type": "page",
    "title": "Test page",
    "body": {
        "storage": {
            "value": "<p>bitbucket</p>",
            "representation": "storage"
        }
    }
} {code}
 # Refresh the page in the UI and you will see that the text switched from "confluence" to "bitbucket" in View mode.
 # Click on 'Edit' to edit the page.

h3. Expected Results

The page editor should have been updated to reflect the same content as in View mode.
{quote}bitbucket
{quote}
h3. Actual Results

The page editor shows this as the shared draft:
{quote}bitbkjirat
{quote}
h3. Workaround

Ensure that before you update the page via API, all unpublished drafts are published first. This will then result in the page and draft to be correctly updated.

h3. Summary

In older versions of Confluence (4.x), the default value for this parameter was set to *10s* but it is now set to *30s*.

I see this mentioned in [DaisyHtmlDiffer.java|https://stash.atlassian.com/projects/CONF/repos/confluence/browse/confluence-core/confluence/src/java/com/atlassian/confluence/diff/DaisyHtmlDiffer.java#67] as well:
{code:java}
    private static final String TIMEOUT_PROPERTY = "confluence.html.diff.timeout";

    /**
     * Defaults to 30 seconds.  Rendering two pages and then diffing them can take quite a while.
     */
    private static final int TIMEOUT = Integer.getInteger(TIMEOUT_PROPERTY, 30000);{code}
The page to update is [Recognized System Properties|https://confluence.atlassian.com/doc/recognized-system-properties-190430.html#RecognizedSystemProperties-confluence.html.diff.timeout].

h3. Problem Definition  
* Currently there is no way of creating a task from a comment;

h3. Suggested Solution  
* Add the alternative to create tasks and assign them to users from a page's comment;

h3. Why this is important   
* By adding this functionality we prevent redundancy in having to add the same comment in a page to the page itself just so we can create a task. This way tasks can be created in other scenarios too.
